        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were the vain son of a minor Italian nobleman in the resort town of Ravenna.  Your embrace was unexpected.  Your father had long managed the affairs of the local Lasombra and one of them took a fancy to your beauty.  The affair was brief and tragic, for though others often noticed your appearance, your reflection was lost to you and your rank of honor within the Sabbat was of little import to you.  When your Sire was raised up as an Inquistor you aided him in his hunt for heresey and infernalism and that is when you hit upon the power that coudl restore your lost visage. At first you thought you could control the demonic power, but soon found yourself a slave to the demon Irritum.  You regained your reflection, but you no longer held the blood of the Lasombra Clan in your veins.  It was only your Sire's great power that freed you from the pact.  At first you thought he must have captured the demon, but now you believe he made a pact of his own to free you from slavery.  Your sire sent you away to form your own pack and it has been almost two decades since you saw him last.  You've rededicated your self to the Dark Father and have relinquished all human cares and wants with a vow of poverty to Caine.  You've come to San Diego to launch a new Crusade and form the Sabbat into a unified and pure chorus that will call forth the fires of Gehenna."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Judge Inquisitor Bertolli Cinqo",
          "Reference: (If any)",
